EVALUATE***Grading***
GRADER MAY ALSO BE WRONG
o ask a chatbot to grade a student’s solution to a task, first ask the chatbot to work out the solution on its own. Then ask it to compare with the student’s solution. Then decide if the student’s solution is correct. Then, if the student’s solution is incorrect, ask it to give hints.

The chatbot as a grader may get the solution wrong as well, so try more than one chatbot, and also review the results yourself to get an idea of what kinds of questions/problems each chatbot is able to properly grade.


***Qualitative Scoring***
For open ended essays, such a debate arguments, you can ask a chatbot to give a numeric score. First ask the chatbot to list out its criteria before giving its numeric score based on its listed criteria.

Model graded evaluation: You can ask a chatbot to evaluate the quality of another chatbot’s output. Evaluation of other models, such as an image classifier, are more straightforward when there are only a few distinct categories for the output, or when the output of the model is a number. Large language models output open ended text, so evaluating them is more difficult because you don’t have a single “right answer” to compare it to. There is a lot to consider when evaluating the quality of chatbots, but one way to get started is to ask another chatbot to perform this evaluation.


