***Chat: How its going***
To encourage the chatbot to have a two-way conversation, consider the following instructions:

“leave the conversation open for additional follow-ups”.

To encourage the chatbot to only output what it wants you to read or hear, consider adding:

“Do not output your internal monologue.”

You can also give the chatbot a role that is suitable for the conversation. For instance, describe its role as a life coach in terms of how it responds to the client (active listening as opposed to problem solving).

You can first get a sense of how the chatbot performs by default, and add more instructions to guide its behavior.


