***Chat: Mock Interview***
Give the chatbot the role of an interviewer, and provide the job description.

Describe the interviewer’s task: ask questions one at a time (instead of listing out all questions at once). Choose a limit to the number of questions the interviewer will ask before concluding the interview.

Describe the interview process: Instruct the interviewer to ask follow-up questions based on the interviewee’s responses. Wait for the interviewee to respond before moving onto the next prepared interview question. (Sometimes a chatbot may ask both the follow up question and the next prepared question without giving the interviewee time to respond to the follow-up question). Conclude the interview after asking all prepared questions (and follow-up questions).

Give feedback: ask the interviewer to give feedback and a numeric score for each answer to the prepared questions.


